This is my tribute to the nice girls. To the nice girls who are overlooked, who become friends and nothing more, who spend hours fixating upon their looks and their personalities and their actions because it must be they that are doing something wrong. 

This is for the girls who don't give it up on the first date, who don't want to play mind games, who provide a comforting hug and a supportive audience for a story they've heard a thousand times. 

This is for the girls who understand that they aren't perfect and that the guys they're interested in aren't either, for the girls who flirt and laugh and worry and obsess over the slightest glance, whisper, touch, because somehow they are able to keep alive that hope that maybe... maybe this time he'll have understood. This is an homage to the girls who laugh loud and often, who are comfortable in skirts and sweats and combat boots, who care more than they should for guys who don't deserve their attention. 

This is for those girls who have been in the trenches, who have watched other girls time and time again fake up and make up and fuck up the guys in their lives without saying a word. 

This is for the girls who have been there from the beginning and have heard the rite words of advice, from "there are plenty of fish in the sea," to "time heals all wounds." This is to honor those girls who know that guys are just as scared as they are, who know that they deserve better, who are seeking to find it.


This is for the girls who have never been in love, but know that it's an experience that they don't want to miss out on. For the girls who have sought a night with friends and been greeted by a night of catcalling, rude L0VESzs and explicit invitations that they'd rather not have experienced. 

This is for the girls who have spent their weekends sitting on the sidelines of a beer pong tournament or a case race, or playing Florence Nightingale for a vomiting guy friend or a comatose crush, who have received a drunk phone call just before dawn from someone who doesn't care enough to invite them over but is still willing to pass out in their bed. 

This is for the girls who have left sad song lyrics in their away messages, who have tried to make someone understand through a subliminally appealing profile, who have time and time again dropped their male friend hint after hint after hint only to watch him chase after the first blonde girl in a skirt. 

This is for the girls who have been told that they're too good or too smart or too pretty, who have been given compliments as a way of breaking off a relationship, who have ever been told they are only wanted as a friend.

This one's for the girls who you can take home to mom, but won't because it's easier to sleep with a whore than foster a relationship; this is for the girls who have been led on by words and kisses and touches, all of which were either only true for the moment, or never real to begin with. 

This is for the girls who have allowed a guy into their head and heart and bed, only to discover that he's just not ready, he's just not over her, he's just not looking to be tied down; this is for the girls who believe the excuses because it's easier to believe that it's not that they don't want you, it's that they don't want anyone. 

This is for the girls who have had their hearts broken and their hopes dashed by someone too cavalier to have cared in the first place; this is for the nights spent dissecting every word and syllable and inflection in his speech, for the nights when you've returned home alone, for the nights when you've seen from across the room him leaning a little too close, or standing a little too near, or talking a little too softly for the girl he's with to be a random hookup. 

This is for the girls who have endured party after party in his presence, finally having realized that it wasn't that he didn't want a relationship: it was that he didn't want you. I honor you for the night his dog died or his grandmother died or his little brother crashed his car and you held him, thinking that if you only comforted him just right, or said the right words, or rubbed his back in the right way then perhaps he'd realize what it was that he already had. This is for the night you realized that it would never happen, and the sunrise you saw the next morning after failing to sleep.


This is for the "I really like you, so let's still be friends" kiss after you read more into a situation than he ever intended; this is for never realizing that when you choose friends, you seldom choose those which make you cry yourself to sleep. This is for the hugs you've received from your female friends, for the nights they've reassured you that you are beautiful and intelligent and amazing and loyal and truly worthy of a great guy; this is for the despair you all felt as you sat in the aftermath of your tears, knowing that that night the only companionship you'd have was with a pillow and your teddy bear. 

This is for the girls who have been used and abused, who have endured what he was giving because at least he was giving something; this is for the stupidity of the nights we've believed that something was better than nothing, though his something was nothing we'd have ever wanted. 

This is for the girls who have been satisified with too little and who have learned never to expect anything more: for the girls who don't think that they deserve more, because they've been conditioned for so long to accept the scraps thrown to them by guys.


This is what I don't understand. Men sit and question and whine that girls are only attracted to the mean guys, the guys who berate them and belittle them and don't appreciate them and don't want them; who use them for sex and think of little else than where their next conquest will be made. Men complain that they never meet nice girls, girls who are genuinely interested and compelling, who are intelligent and sweet and smart and beautiful; men despair that no good women want to share in their lives, that girls play mindgames, that girls love to keep them hanging. Yet, men, I ask you: were you to meet one of these genuinely interested, thrillingly compelling, interesting and intelligent and sweet and beautiful and smart girls, were you to give her your number and wait for her to call... and if you were to receive a call from her the next day and she, in her truthful, loyal, intelligent and straightforward nice girl fashion, were to tell you that she finds you intriguing and attractive and interesting and worth her time and perhaps material from which she could fashion a boyfriend, would you or would you not immediately call your friends to tell them of the "stalker chick" you'd met the night prior, who called you and wore her heart on her sleeve and told the truth? And would you, or would you not, refuse to make plans with her, speak with her, see her again, and once again return to the bar or club or party scene and search once more for this "nice girl" who you just cannot seem to find? Because therein lies the truth, guys: we nice girls are everywhere. But you're not looking for a nice girl. You're not looking for someone genuinely interested in your intermural basketball game, or your anatomy midterm grade, or that argument you keep having with your father; you're looking for a quick fix, a night when you can pretend to have a connection with another human being which is just as disposable as the condom you were using during it.


So don't say you're on the lookout for nice girls, guys, when you pass us up on every step you take. Sometimes we go undercover; sometimes we go in disguise: sometimes when that girl in the low cut shirt or the too tight miniskirt won't answer your catcalls, sometimes you're looking at a nice girl in whore's clothing - - we might say we like the attention, we might blush and giggle and turn back to our friends, but we're all thinking the same thing: "This isn't me. Tomorrow morning, I'll be wearing a teeshirt and flannel shorts, I'll have slept alone and I'll be making my hungover best friend breakfast. See through the disguise. See me." You never do. Why? Because you only see the exterior, you only see the slutty girl who welcomes those advances. You don't want the nice girl.. so don't say you're looking for a relationship: relationships take time and energy and intent, three things we're willing to extend - - but in return, we're looking for compassion and loyalty and trust, three things you never seem willing to express. Maybe nice guys finish last, but in the race they're running they're chasing after the whores and the sluts and the easy-targets... the nice girls are waiting at the finish line with water and towels and a congradulatory hug (and yes, if she's a nice girl and she likes you, the sweatiness probably won't matter), hoping against hope that maybe you'll realize that they're the ones that you want at the end of that silly race.


So maybe it won't last forever. Maybe some of those guys in that race will turn in their running shoes and make their way to the concession stand where we're waiting; however, until that happens, we still have each other, that silly race to watch, and all the chocolate we can eat (because what's a concession stand at a race without some chocolate?)

"Blue Chair" 
There's a blue rocking chair
Sitting in the sand
Weathered by the storms and well oiled hands
It sways back and forth
With the help of the winds
It seems to always be there, like an old trusted friend.

Chorus:
I've read a lot of books, wrote a few songs
Looked at my life - where it's goin', where it's gone
I've seen the world through a bus windshield
But nothing compares to the way that I see it

When I sit in that old blue chair.

From that chair I've caught a few fish and some rays
And I've watched boats sail in and out of Cinnamon Bay
I let go of a lover that took a piece of my heart
Prayed many times for forgiveness and a brand new start.

I've read a lot of books, wrote a few songs

This weekend was sooo fun! You dont even know..

Friday

Adam called me and then i went over to his appartment and hung out with him and hes room mate Chris! They were playing Halo 2 and we were all just having a good time. He has the fattest cat i have ever seen in my entire life! It is huge! His name is Chubb Chubb. Its soo cute! Then we all went to see White noise. I liked it, minus the ending, that was kinda bad. It made me jump a few times tho. Then we went to go get some food and then we went back to his appartment/townhouse. And just watched the Jamie Kenendy show. It was fun.

Saturday

I went to work at like 10 and then me and Ashley went to Detroit! It was a lot of fun. My friend Chris's band was playing. (not the chris from the night before) The bands called The Summer Formal, and they're really really good. I couldnt belive it. There was a band called Finius there and they were sweet too. Ashley got us lost a little bit.. lol and it was funny, i was gettin so mad.. im such a loser.. but its all good.  We had to pay like fucking $12 to park! i was like holy shit! But it was worth it. We got to hang out with the band and stuff. And Ashley fell in love with the singer Nick. I have to admit he is way hot. He wears girls pants, and thats just hott! I wanted to stay and party with them but by that time we werent going to get home until like 1 anyway so we just left. On the way home we listened to my old Jonesday tape! It brought back so many old memories. It was a good time. It was so funny to watch Ashley get that excited. It was good times

Sunday

I woke up early and me and Denny went to meet up with Paw, Josh, and Chachie! And we all went Detroit ( yea it was that kind of weekend) to check out the Auto show. I had the best time. They make me laugh so hard its rediculus. I was acting like i was from Manchester England the entire time and people believed me. Two guys asked me where i was from and Denny had to walk away  because he was laughing so hard. I swear i havent laughed as much ive laughed this weekend is so long i cant even remember. But then we all came back, and we were taking pictures in the car. I'll post them when Denny gives them to me! They are soo funny! But then we went to get bubble tea in EL. It was so funny. I guess you had to be there but thats going in my memory book forever as one of the best times of my life. No joke. Then i got home and it wasnt good. Me and my mom kind of bonded and we got stuff sorted out. But im really worried about her. Ive been praying all day for her. She needs it. So even if you dont believe in  God, will you please pray for her. I would really appriciate it. 

Monday

I was supposed to go to this MLK day thing, which i was really interested in. But the events from the night before got me down a little bit, so i didnt end up going. I got all my laundry and stuff done, so i guess thats a good thing. Today was kind of just a chill day. It was nice. Im really thankful for the things that Martin Luther King Jr. did for all of us. He really was a great man and he will live forever through the people hes touched. Its really amamzing. Ive been thinking about this stuff lately. I want to be known forever for doing something great. Like in my Western Civ class we were talking about Socrates and Alexandar the Great, and they lived soo long ago, and yet we still hear and learn about them. I want that. Maybe someday ill have that. 

well as for the rest of the week, i really dont have any plans. I have to study for finals but thats it, oh and I have to study for my ACT's. I know I know.. im a loser for not taking them before. I just thought I was going to go to LCC, but now that im going to Ferris i need them, so im taking them. Better late then never right.. well thats all, im kinda burned out. Hope you all have a good night. And dont forget to pray for my mom! Thank you. 

"In the end, we will remember not the words of our enimies, but the silence of our friends." - Martin Luther King Jr.

Tell her you think shes AMAZING. Tell her why you think shes so  amazing.  Play with her hair. Talk to her in movie theatres. Snuggle, Hold her hand, and lightly KISS her. Hold her hand and walk. Hold  her hand and run. Just hold her hand. Pick flowers from other  peoples yards and give them to her. Tell her she looks BEAUTIFUL. Introduce her  to your friends as "The most amazing girl I know''. Sit in the park and talk to her.  Take her to the library, ice skating, playgrounds, and coffee shops. Tell her stupid jokes... Whatever it takes to make her laugh. Write poems about her. Walk with her, even if its just around the block. Throw pebbles at her window at night. SURPRISE HER. Do things that make her SMILE, make her LAUGH, and make her want to KISS you right on the face. BE SPONTANEOUS.. When she starts yelling at you, tell her you love her. Give her back rubs. Play football with her. Let her fall asleep in your arms. Call her even if its just to say hi. Call her back if she calls you. Jump on the bed with her.  Whisper in her ear. Sing to her, no matter how bad you are. Carve your names into a tree. Get her mad, then KISS her. Push her on swings. Stay up with her all night. Leave her little unexpected notes.. on the car, or on her door, saying how much she means to you. Take her to romantic places and lay out blankets to look at the *stars*. Make up nicknames for each other. Show up at her work or apartment unexpectedly. Send flowers and dorky notes that only you two understand. Teach her guitar. Lend her your cds. Make her cds of songs that remind you of her. Write her letters. If she asks you to go to a show with her, go, even if it means a 5 hour car trip. Go on a road trip even if theres no destination or you cant be gone long. Listen to her favorite songs. When shes sad or sick, hang out with her or stay on the phone with her, even if shes not saying anything.  Buy her ice cream. Let her take all the pictures of you SHE WANTS. Look into her eyes. Slow dance with her, even if the music is fast. Make her a romantic dinner for special days. Remember dates.. even ones like your first kiss or date and surprise her on the anniversary. Kiss her in the rain. Kiss her when she least expects it

I dont know what makes me do the things i do. I dont think about things before i do them... i think about it after... Why cant i just be one of the guys! lol not litteraly.. but why cant i just hang out with people anymore... i dont understand how life got to be this complicated.. 

I truely wouldnt change a lot of things in my life because its those situations that have made me into the person that i am.. even if i dont like my self that much at times. But i realized that everyone hates them self at one point or another. I am no different. There are some lustful relationships that i would take back, I know i hurt people, but for some reason or another at that point in time i didnt care. And now i look back and im shocked at how i acted. Im sorry to those who have felt that from me. I never really ment to do the things i have done.. and i hope one day you'll realize that your a much better person not with me... rather then with me. 

I am a strong person. And i think thats what makes people want to be around me.. and at other times it makes them hate me. I understand that. But sometimes I need to realize that my actions speek louder then words.. and how i treat people needs to change. i hold hate in my heart for too long and i need God to help me get rid of it. But maybe im waiting too long and looking up to much... maybe i need to do things on my own for a little bit. You know i havent really ever gone that long with out a relationship... I think its because for some reason or another i need to feel loved.. and i dont mean friendship love.. i just mean love. Real love. And ive never really had that.. besides one person who i think, thinks he loves me... But in all acutuallity he doesnt. Havent you ever be so in love with someone.. so blinded by it.. because you think its so wonderful, then you have a fight and break up or just stop talking and realize that the person that you were with, wasnt really the person you knew. That they did all these bad things. But you just didnt see their faults because you were blinded. 

I dont want to be blinded by lust anymore... Im 17 years old. I have a lot of happiness thats is a head for me. And i just want to be me for a little bit.. If i have to find out who i am alone.. then thats what i need to do. I need to find God agian. Its so funny, that i never give credit to the big man when things are going good... but when times are bad all i can do is blame him. Its not his fault.. he gave me free will... and now i need to take it back.. 


I really am happy. Yes there are things in my life that i need to change to make me a better person, and friends i need to keep and friends i need to get rid of.. it seems like all my hate and hostility comes from wanting to be someone im not.. or to be around people that might not give me what i need. 
I just need to realize that everything will be ok in the end.. and if its not ok.. then its not the end... and i need to realize that no one is perfect.. that people are just like me.. people who forget to call friends.. even when they need them.. and people who make mistakes and say things that they shouldnt.. i need to become a better person.. and i will... so dont worry about me.. God will take care of me.. I think everyone needs to find out who they are, and what they need, before trying to help someone else...


I love you..

If you think about it.. Everyone makes choices in their lives. Whether it be good or bad..

Everyone knows that when you drink and drive you can get hurt or hurt others.. But they did it anyway. I wish that they thought about it before stepping in that car.. But they didnt.. and now they have to live with the choices they made.. 

Its just sad that someone had to die.. I Feel sorry for them and for the families. Because the choices that they made today.. are the regrets they have to live with tomorrow.. 

I hope that they ones who lived.. learned. I know that sounds cliche but its true..

Whats the point of going through school and meeting some of the best people in the world.. and then one night you drink.. for whatever reason.. and step into a car and die... without knowing what you could be or what you could have done.. it just seems like a waste of time..  

We've lost to many people this way. Doesnt it just seem easier to not drive.. I know people are going to drink or whatever and do what they want.. But just dont drive if your going to do it. Stay at the place where you are drinking.. Because the next time you step in to a car after drinking.. you could kill your self.. or even your best friend..

Me and someone else got in a really big fight.. we have never faught like that. It was a whole bunch of talking about what the other person has done wrong. I always blame other people for my problems. And I know I bring a lot of the drama in to our groups. But I never intend to do that. We all have our problems.. but sometimes I feel like all the fingers are pointing in my direction, because im an easy target. Nobody can say that they are drama free all the time.. and I usally have at least one thing that is going on. And some people have asked me why I dont talk about my problems with people. And why I only let a select few in to "my" world. Well I am going to put it all out there...

I DO NOT trust people. Some of it is my past but most of it, is what people are doing right now. I feel like NO one ever see's the good I've done for people. And they dont see that really I try to be a good person. I really do care about my friends! With my whole heart. I love each and everyone of you for who you are.. and i dont usually judge what bad ive seen in you. But I feel like there is ALWAYS someone mad at me.. for whatever reason there is. I know I have said and done some pretty stupid shit in my day. But DO NOT hold that aginst me now. I am totally different then I was one year ago.. Just like ADULF said in her journal. Im growing up. Im going to make friends along the way. Some people will not like me.. and i know that.. I know I can be a bitch. But maybe I'm just blunt. I say whats on my mind. So you always know what I think of you.. Or of what you say. I know a lot of people arent really used to it but i have always been this way. WHY ARE PEOPLE ACTING LIKE ITS A NEW THING???? 

Someone once told a friend of mine that the reason he liked me so much was because I dont like people walk all over me and he thought i could keep him in check. And I do, do that. But why does this person care so much what I think? And then when I do say what I think.. They get all pissed off.. I dont understand. I know its not what you say.. its now you say it. I know that i say it in hurtful ways. But if this person really thought we were friends then, I would think, they would know i never tried to hurt them like that. And sometimes i say things that i think.. before thinking about if its going to hurt that person. Im sorry if i hurt you. And I hope you do know I care about you. 

Sometimes I feel like im at the edge of a cliff and my friends are on the other side just trying to push me off. None of my friends know i feel like that.. Becaues i dont want to hurt them. And its not everytime we hang out.. its only like once in a while.. But... When it happens its usally when everyone starts attacking me. And ive talked to some of my friends about this.. so i dont want them to think im keeping it going.. just some of the other people need to read this. 

I put up my walls because I have to.. or I'll have nothing to protect my self with. 

The only thing holding you back from your future.. is you past.  So let it go. 

And the only reason I put that in there is because i need to live by that.. 

Sometimes i want to move away from everyone and go to a place where NO ONE knows who i am .. so i can start over. I know i cant do that.. So i rather just start over Here.

Alright a lot of people have been discussing Gays. Everyone has an opinion. Just because some one doesnt think the way you do doesnt mean that person is a bad person. And if Annie backs up her story with evidence that she thinks is right that doesnt make her a bad person ether. I think its easier sometimes for people to point their fingers at people who are different from them. Maybe because the person who is pointing the finger is the one with the insecurities. I personally think that gay people should be able to get married. They are people too and people deserve to be happy! Just because they are gay doesnt make them a bad person either. That is ONE thing about that person. Its NOT WHO they are. You can not help who you fall in love with. I honestly can say that i believe that gay people are born gay. Because every gay person i have ever met has told me that they have known that they were gay since they can remember. ANd I dont care how many studies you show me saying that it is something chemically wrong with them, I will not believe it. If this is a country where everyone is free to practice what ever religion they want to, but with out killing anything or hurting anyone, then why cant gays get married? Who are they hurting? 50 years ago it was not right for races to mix. We now look back and say how stupid that was. In 10 years we are going to look back and say how stupid it was for people not to let Gays get married. This problem is NOT going to go away. So why not let people who love each other get married? What if the government suddenly said that you and the person that you loved could not get married... You would fight it til death do you part.... In order for people to understand, something has got to happen.. Just like the Civil Rights movement.. Protest started, And protest have started now. I just rather be on the side of people who want people to be happy.. Not the ones who try to hold someone back from being happy because they dont agree with something (that has NOTHING to do with them) about a person... These are my thoughts.. Love them or Hate them.. But they are my own.. NOT yours.
